snippet: Mrs. Clinton may face a dilemma as she recounts her record before a possible White House bid: Much of her work as secretary of state either is unfinished or went awry.
abstract: Hillary Clinton is struggling to define accomplishments during her tenure as secretary of state, since much of what she labored over is either unfinished business or has gone awry in Pres Obama's second term; aides say her legacy is defined not by clear victories but by a dogged commitment to the process; advocates say, because of her celebrity and potential political future, Clinton is held to a different standard than other secretaries of state.

byline.original: By MARK LANDLER and AMY CHOZICK
byline.contributor: Mark Landler reported from Washington, and Amy Chozick from New York.

lead_paragraph: Mrs. Clinton may face a dilemma as she recounts her record before a possible White House bid: Much of her work as secretary of state either is unfinished or went awry.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Struggles to Define a Legacy in Progress
headline.print_headline: Clinton Struggles to Define a Legacy in Progress
